Name: UCSB
Description: A great university located along the California coast!

Name: Empire State Building
Description: A massive tower in New York City that was built in the 1930s.

Name: LA Memorial Coliseum
Description: An outdoor sports stadium that was built in the 1920s and is currently used as the USC football arena.

Name: Alcatraz Island
Description: A decommissioned federal prison, now national historic landmark, located in the middle of San Francisco Bay.

Name: Mount Rushmore
Description: A massive sculpture of former US presidents George Washington, Thomas Jefferson, Theodore Roosevelt, and Abraham Lincoln.

Name: Zero Milestone
Description: A marker in Washinton DC that was originally intended to be the initial milestone from which all US road distances were to be reckoned.
